rComments: Articulate, witty and interesting lecturer with an obvious background in int'l law. VERY organized; course had two instructors but was better administered than many others with only one. Friendly & approachable. Tests are unique and challenging; open-book with fact patterns. Readings essential; lectures tend to mostly expand on & explain readings.

Great lecturer and very helpful, breaks down the material well so makes it interesting and less dry. But the other lecturer in this course is not quite as much, so I find that many students show up for his class but you can see that there are significantly fewer students when the other teaches.

He follows the textbook really closely, but still his lectures  are really helpful. Its really easy to get B or B+, but to get an A you need to really put in effort. Even if not to learn, you should go to the lectures just to experience his laugh. Its one of a kind!!! Kennedy's a great prof!!!

Not the Gerard Kennedy you're probably thinking of. He explains key concepts really well. The lectures and readings are similar, but complimentary, so both are necessary for success. His nerdy laugh and sounds are pretty funny.
